1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION directing the Legislative Research Commission
2 to establish the Kentucky School for the Deaf Governance Task Force.
3 WHEREAS, the Kentucky School for the Deaf was created by the Kentucky
4 General Assembly on April 10, 1823; and
5 WHEREAS, the Kentucky School for the Deaf was the first institution of its kind
6 established west of the Allegheny Mountains and the first to be supported by public
7 funds; and
8 WHEREAS, the General Assembly is committed to meeting the educational needs
9 of Kentucky's deaf and hard of hearing student population; and
10 WHEREAS, the General Assembly has the responsibility of ensuring that the
11 current governance model for the Kentucky School for the Deaf is not hindering student
12 achievement and is appropriately representing the interests of its constituency; and
13 WHEREAS, the General Assembly, in fulfillment of its obligations, wishes to
14 assess the efficiency and effectiveness of a possible independent board of education to
15 govern operations of the Kentucky School for the Deaf;
16 NOW, THEREFORE,
17 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the General Assembly of the
18 Commonwealth of Kentucky, the Senate concurring therein:
19 Section 1. The Legislative Research Commission is hereby directed to establish
20 the Kentucky School for the Deaf Governance Task Force. The task force shall:
21 (1) Study and make recommendations to identify opportunities for improving the
22 governance of the Kentucky School for the Deaf; and
23 (2) Assess the efficiency and effectiveness of different models of governance,
24 including but not limited to an independent board of education.
25 Section 2. The Kentucky School for the Deaf Governance Task Force shall be
26 composed of the following members, with final membership being subject to the
27 consideration and approval of the Legislative Research Commission:
