1 (1) Three members of the House of Representatives to be appointed by the
2 Speaker of the House, one of whom shall be designated to serve as co-chair;
3 (2) Three members of the Senate to be appointed by the President of the Senate,
4 one of whom shall be designated to serve as co-chair;
5 (3) One member of the House of Representatives to be appointed by the Minority
6 Floor Leader of the House of Representatives;
7 (4) One member of the Senate to be appointed by the Minority Floor Leader of
8 the Senate;
9 (5) One member who is the parent or guardian of a child that attends the
10 Kentucky School for the Deaf;
11 (6) One member who is a certified teacher currently or formerly employed as a
12 classroom teacher at the Kentucky School for the Deaf, who has at least five years of
13 experience working at the school; and
14 (7) Two members with a background, knowledge, skills, or experience in the field
15 of deaf education or American Sign Language.
16 Section 3. The Kentucky School for the Deaf Governance Task Force shall
17 meet as necessary during the 2025 Interim of the General Assembly. The task force shall
18 submit any findings and recommendations to the Legislative Research Commission for
19 referral to the appropriate committee or committees by December 1, 2025.
20 Section 4. Provisions of this Resolution to the contrary notwithstanding, the
21 Legislative Research Commission shall have the authority to alternatively assign the
22 issues identified herein to an interim joint committee or subcommittee thereof, and to
23 designate a study completion date.
